13
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:10,000
Can you tell us about your family growing up in Jamaica?

14
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:17,000
Yes, I could, if it were necessary.

15
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:25,000
My father as a young man came to the United States and spent some time, some considerable time there.

16
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:29,000
I was quite a legend as I walked through New York, through Harlem.

17
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:34,000
People say, here is sun, here is sun and there are a lot of stories about my father.

18
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:39,000
He was a very dramatic figure.

19
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:45,000
He had a deep boom in laugh, an obvious love of people.

20
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:55,000
He was six foot four, 240 pounds, which in that day on the edge made him a giant.

21
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:02,000
Or he was a professional footballer, lying back today.

22
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:10,000
In this country, he was a motorcycle race, with a motorcycle very big back in the 30s and 40s.

23
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:13,000
And a trick writer.

24
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:20,000
He went back to Jamaica, entered politics, was elected in his constituency.

25
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:26,000
It was very, very popular with the people, look at his generous and kind.

26
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:35,000
And people said if he hadn't died at age of 44, he probably would have been Prime Minister of the country.

27
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:46,000
And there was much speculation that death was a consequence of political conspiracies and wickedness, which is the way people tended to think.

28
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:52,000
My mother was an amazing woman because she brought the thru of herself after my father died.

29
00:02:52,000 --> 00:03:03,000
I was interested, so a lot of his property was hung up, all kinds of litigation and bureaucracy.

30
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:12,000
And she raised three children, sent us to the best school in the country.

31
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:22,000
My brother became an engineer, went to University of Michigan on an athletic scholarship.

32
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:28,000
And he was six foot five and very black.

33
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:31,000
And he was an excellent athlete.

34
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:37,000
