171
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:02,000
Then there was segregation in Maryland, there was segregation in Virginia.

172
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:07,000
So you could drive out to the district of Columbia and have, you know, bona fide sit-ins.

173
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:15,000
And so it's, it's a failure of our responsibility to do history if the students are told they're an active in that way.

174
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:17,000
That's number one.

175
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:25,000
Number two, there were professors here, unfortunately, there's a historian whose name I'm not going to remember,

176
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:33,000
who gave us very contemporary readings, political readings.

177
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:40,000
And there was a quality, there was a level of instruction among certain of the faculty there.

178
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:49,000
That was very focused on social issues and very focused on educating the assessor of the state of the world.

179
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:57,000
And in addition to which, a health percentage of the African American students came out of this deep southerner.

180
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:04,000
For example, there were slave sellers who came from South Carolina into Nug.

181
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:10,000
And Cleve was sent to hold by his parents because white folks had won them in the community.

182
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:14,000
That is, he continued to agitate in the way he was agitated.

183
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:17,000
And he was probably going to come to a very bad end.

184
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:19,000
So they sent him or to hold to safety.

185
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:23,000
And the first thing he does is he's drunk afterwards to put some giants in Nug.

186
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:26,000
You know, and comes back, don't so.

187
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:30,000
And that was also true of Hank Thomas, Henry Thomas.

188
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:34,000
Henry Thomas came from Fort Augustine, Florida.

189
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:44,000
And he maintained a constant protest against the discrimination in a part that surrounded them there.

190
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:49,000
As a matter of fact, a friend of his joined over the department, Clay Thelbenjerman,

191
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:52,000
and said, you know, he and Frank were very close growing up.

192
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:58,000
So, principally, he said, the only entertainment we had in Fort Augustin was to go to the movies on a Saturday.

193
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:02,000
Well, we had to sit up in the cross-ness and the segregated era.

